  <front>
   <head>Enoch Arden</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="blank verse">
     <l n="1" met="++-++--+-+-">Long lines of cliff breaking have left a chasm;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+--+-+-+">And in the chasm are foam and yellow sands;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+++-+-+-+">Beyond red roofs about a narrow wharf</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+-+-+-+-+-">In cluster; then a mouldered church; and higher</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+++-+++-+">A long street climbs to one tall-towered mill;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+-+--+--++">And high in heaven behind it a gray down</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+-+-+-+">With Danish barrows; and a hazel wood,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+-+-+">By autumn nutters haunted, flourishes</l>
     <l n="9" met="+--+++---+|+--+-+-+-+">Green in a cuplike hollow of the down.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
